The original accepted answer mentions [jquery.cookie plugin](https://github.com/carhartl/jquery-cookie). A few months ago though, it was renamed to [js-cookie](https://github.com/js-cookie/js-cookie) and the jQuery dependency removed. One of the reasons was just to make it easy to integrate with other frameworks, like Angular.

Now, if you want to integrate [js-cookie](https://github.com/js-cookie/js-cookie) with angular, it is as easy as something like:

    module.factory( &quot;cookies&quot;, function() {
      return Cookies.noConflict();
    });

And that&#39;s it. No jQuery. No ngCookies.

